casebody.data:
Cornelia Gilman, Respondent v. Preble Tucker, Appellant. Decided January 5, 1891. Appeal by defendant from judgment entered upon findings, etc., at special term. Tucker, Hardy & Wainwright, for appellant. George H. Fletcher, for respondent.

Before Sedgwick, Ch. J., Freedman and Ingraham, JJ.

Per Curiam.

Judgment affirmed, with costs.
